Based on the sample provided, it covers only a subset of the DVLA derivation scenarios.

Covered scenarios:

* Full licence entitlement (`entitlements_type = F`)
* Non B/BE entitlement path (`entitlements_code = Q`)
* Entitlement validFrom date populated
* Licence status = FC
* Single endorsement present (`SP30`)
* Disqualification period = PT0S (no ban / less than 1 month bucket)
* isDisqual = FALSE
* Single endorsement points (`noOfPoints = 3`)
* Offence date populated

Not covered:

* Entitlement derivation paths involving:

  * F + B
  * F + BE
  * P + B
  * P + BE
* Multiple entitlements for the same driver (priority and validFrom selection logic)
* Conviction code lookup mappings (e.g. AC20→AC10, BA20→BA10, CD70→CD40)
* Disqualification buckets:

  * P2M (1–3 months)
  * P6M (4–12 months)
  * P2Y (13+ months)
* Multiple endorsements for the same driver
* Validation of noOfPoints aggregation logic (sum of endorsement points)
* Multiple drivers within the same quote (DriverPRN-level validation)
* Current vs Original message scenarios
* Additional licence status mappings (e.g. PC)

Recommendation:

To achieve good coverage without creating excessive test data, the following additional samples would be sufficient:

1. F + B entitlement scenario
2. P + B entitlement scenario
3. Driver with multiple endorsements (e.g. 3 + 6 points)
4. Conviction code lookup scenario (e.g. AC20, BA20, CD70)
5. P2M, P6M and P2Y disqualification period scenarios
6. Quote containing multiple drivers (multiple DriverPRNs)

This would cover the main derivation branches and edge cases defined in the requirement.
